{
  "info": {
    "name": "Super Banking \u2014 1-Exchange Step-by-Step (RFC 8693)",
    "description": "Super Banking 1-Exchange Delegated Chain \u2014 Step-by-Step (RFC 8693)\n\nAudience: Learners, workshop participants.\nPairs with: BX-Finance-Shared.postman_environment.json\n\nWalks through each OAuth/OIDC step individually so you can inspect tokens at every stage.\n\nToken chain:\n  Step 1:   Authorization Code + PKCE (pi.flow) \u2192 Subject Token (aud = ENDUSER_AUDIENCE)\n  Step 2:   RFC 8693 Token Exchange #1 \u2192 MCP Token (act.sub = PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID)\n  Step 3:   Client Credentials \u2192 PingOne API Token\n  Step 4:   User Lookup (PingOne Management API)\n\nRun steps in order. Tokens are automatically saved to collection variables by test scripts.\n\nPrerequisites:\n  1. Import and select BX-Finance-Shared.postman_environment.json as the active environment.\n  2. Fill all required variables in the environment file.\n  3. Run Utility B (Set mayAct) once per test user before Step 2.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Your PingOne environment UUID"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_REGION",
      "value": "com",
      "description": "com | eu | ca | ap"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_ID",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client ID \u2014 Super Banking User app"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client ID \u2014 Super Banking Banking App"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_SECRET",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client Secret \u2014 Super Banking Banking App"
    },
    {
      "key": "MCP_CLIENT_ID",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client ID \u2014 Super Banking MCP Service"
    },
    {
      "key": "MCP_CLIENT_SECRET",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client Secret \u2014 Super Banking MCP Service"
    },
    {
      "key": "ENDUSER_AUDIENCE",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Subject Token audience \u2014 set via BX-Finance-Shared environment (ENDUSER_AUDIENCE)"
    },
    {
      "key": "MCP_RESOURCE_URI",
      "value": "",
      "description": "MCP Token audience \u2014 set via BX-Finance-Shared environment (MCP_RESOURCE_URI)"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_API_AUDIENCE",
      "value": "https://api.pingone.com",
      "description": "PingOne API Token audience"
    },
    {
      "key": "subject_token",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 saved by Step 1 test script after Postman completes the PKCE flow"
    },
    {
      "key": "mcp_token",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 set by Step 2"
    },
    {
      "key": "pingone_api_token",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 set by Step 3"
    },
    {
      "key": "user_sub",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 set by Step 1 (user PingOne UUID from sub claim)"
    },
    {
      "key": "TEST_USERNAME",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Username of the test user (used in Step 1b)"
    },
    {
      "key": "TEST_PASSWORD",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Password of the test user (used in Step 1b)"
    },
    {
      "key": "PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_SECRET",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Client Secret of Super Banking User app \u2014 required if token endpoint auth = CLIENT_SECRET_POST"
    },
    {
      "key": "pkce_code_verifier",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 generated by Step 1a pre-request"
    },
    {
      "key": "pkce_code_challenge",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 generated by Step 1a pre-request"
    },
    {
      "key": "flow_id",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 saved by Step 1a from pi.flow response"
    },
    {
      "key": "auth_code",
      "value": "",
      "description": "AUTO \u2014 saved by Step 1c from resume response"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Step 1 \u2014 Subject Token (Headless PKCE via pi.flow)",
      "description": "Gets Token 1 (Subject Token) without a browser using PingOne's `pi.flow` headless mode.\n\nRun sub-requests in order: **1a -> 1b -> 1c -> 1d**\n\nSet `TEST_USERNAME` and `TEST_PASSWORD` in Collection Variables before running.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Step 1a \u2014 GET /authorize (pi.flow, get flowId)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/authorize?response_mode=pi.flow&response_type=code&client_id={{PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_ID}}&scope=openid%20profile%20email%20banking%3Aagent%3Ainvoke&resource={{ENDUSER_AUDIENCE}}&code_challenge={{pkce_code_challenge}}&code_challenge_method=S256",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "auth",
                "pingone",
                "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
                "as",
                "authorize"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "response_mode",
                  "value": "pi.flow"
                },
                {
                  "key": "response_type",
                  "value": "code"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_ID}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "scope",
                  "value": "openid profile email banking:agent:invoke"
                },
                {
                  "key": "resource",
                  "value": "{{ENDUSER_AUDIENCE}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "code_challenge",
                  "value": "{{pkce_code_challenge}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "code_challenge_method",
                  "value": "S256"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Starts the Authorization Code + PKCE flow in headless mode.\n\n`response_mode=pi.flow` tells PingOne to return a JSON flow object instead of redirecting to a browser login page.\n\nThe pre-request script generates a fresh `code_verifier` + `code_challenge` (S256).\n\nOn success PingOne returns `{\"id\": \"<flowId>\", ...}`. The test script saves `flow_id` for Step 1b."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate PKCE code_verifier (64-char URL-safe random string per RFC 7636)",
                  "const chars = 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789-._~';",
                  "let verifier = '';",
                  "for (let i = 0; i < 64; i++) {",
                  "    verifier += chars.charAt(Math.floor(Math.random() * chars.length));",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('pkce_code_verifier', verifier);",
                  "pm.environment.set('pkce_code_verifier', verifier);",
                  "",
                  "// code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(code_verifier))",
                  "const wordArray = CryptoJS.SHA256(verifier);",
                  "const b64       = CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(wordArray);",
                  "const challenge = b64.replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=/g, '');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('pkce_code_challenge', challenge);",
                  "pm.environment.set('pkce_code_challenge', challenge);",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[Step 1a] code_verifier generated:', verifier);",
                  "console.log('[Step 1a] code_challenge:', challenge);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Step 1a: 200 OK \u2014 flow started', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code !== 200) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset('flow_id');",
                  "    pm.environment.unset('flow_id');",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1a] Non-200 response. Not saving flow_id. Response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "    return;",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "if (json.code || json.message) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset('flow_id');",
                  "    pm.environment.unset('flow_id');",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1a] PingOne error payload received. Not saving flow_id. Response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "    return;",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Step 1a: flow object returned', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('_links');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.id) {",
                  "    const now = Date.now();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('flow_id', json.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('flow_id', json.id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('flow_id_issued_at', String(now));",
                  "    pm.environment.set('flow_id_issued_at', String(now));",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1a] flow_id saved:', json.id);",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1a] flow_id_issued_at:', now);",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1a] Flow status:', json.status);",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1a] Next action:', JSON.stringify(json._links || {}));",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1a] No flow id in success payload. Full response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 1b \u2014 POST /flows/{flowId} (submit username + password)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/vnd.pingidentity.usernamePassword.check+json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{TEST_USERNAME}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{TEST_PASSWORD}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/flows/{{flow_id}}",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "auth",
                "pingone",
                "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
                "flows",
                "{{flow_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Submits the user's credentials to the active flow.\n\nThe special Content-Type `application/vnd.pingidentity.usernamePassword.check+json` tells PingOne this is a credential submission.\n\nSet `TEST_USERNAME` and `TEST_PASSWORD` in Collection Variables.\n\nOn success PingOne returns the updated flow object. The test script checks the status and warns if MFA is required."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const flowId = (pm.environment.get('flow_id') || pm.collectionVariables.get('flow_id'));",
                  "if (!flowId || flowId.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1b] flow_id is empty. Run Step 1a first.');",
                  "}",
                  "const issuedAt = Number(pm.environment.get('flow_id_issued_at') || pm.collectionVariables.get('flow_id_issued_at') || 0);",
                  "if (!issuedAt || (Date.now() - issuedAt) > 120000) {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1b] flow_id is stale or missing timestamp. Run Step 1a again immediately before Step 1b.');",
                  "}",
                  "const user = (pm.environment.get('TEST_USERNAME') || pm.collectionVariables.get('TEST_USERNAME'));",
                  "if (!user || user.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1b] TEST_USERNAME is empty. Set it in your active environment.');",
                  "}",
                  "const pass = (pm.environment.get('TEST_PASSWORD') || pm.collectionVariables.get('TEST_PASSWORD'));",
                  "if (!pass || pass.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1b] TEST_PASSWORD is empty. Set it in your active environment.');",
                  "}",
                  "const region = pm.environment.get('PINGONE_REGION') || pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_REGION') || 'com';",
                  "const envId = pm.environment.get('PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID') || pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID');",
                  "console.log(`[Step 1b] POST target: https://auth.pingone.${region}/${envId}/flows/${flowId}`);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Step 1b: 200 OK \u2014 credentials accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 404 && json && json.code === 'NOT_FOUND') {",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1b] NOT_FOUND usually means flow_id is stale/invalid for this environment. Rerun Step 1a, then Step 1b immediately.');",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1b] Response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "    return;",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('[Step 1b] Flow status:', json.status);",
                  "",
                  "if (json.status === 'COMPLETED') {",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1b] Flow COMPLETED \u2014 run Step 1c to get the auth code.');",
                  "} else if (json.status === 'MFA_REQUIRED' || json.status === 'OTP_REQUIRED') {",
                  "    console.warn('[Step 1b] MFA required. This collection does not handle MFA steps. Disable MFA for the test user or use a bypass policy.');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1b] Flow status:', json.status, '| Full response:', JSON.stringify(json, null, 2));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 1c \u2014 GET /as/resume (get auth code from completed flow)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/resume?flowId={{flow_id}}",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "auth",
                "pingone",
                "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
                "as",
                "resume"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "flowId",
                  "value": "{{flow_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Resumes the completed flow and retrieves the authorization code.\n\nPingOne returns `{\"authorizeResponse\": {\"code\": \"...\"}}`.\n\nThe test script saves `auth_code` for Step 1d."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const flowId = (pm.environment.get('flow_id') || pm.collectionVariables.get('flow_id'));",
                  "if (!flowId || flowId.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1c] flow_id is empty. Run Step 1a and 1b first.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Step 1c: 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Step 1c: authorizeResponse.code present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('authorizeResponse');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.authorizeResponse.code).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.authorizeResponse && json.authorizeResponse.code) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_code', json.authorizeResponse.code);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('auth_code', json.authorizeResponse.code);",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1c] auth_code saved. Run Step 1d immediately (codes expire in ~60 seconds).');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1c] No code in response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1c] The flow may not be completed. Check Step 1b status.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 1d \u2014 POST /as/token (exchange code for Subject Token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "authorization_code"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_ID}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{PINGONE_CORE_USER_CLIENT_SECRET}}",
                  "description": "Client Secret of Super Banking User app (required for CLIENT_SECRET_POST token endpoint auth)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "code",
                  "value": "{{auth_code}}",
                  "description": "AUTO \u2014 set by Step 1c"
                },
                {
                  "key": "code_verifier",
                  "value": "{{pkce_code_verifier}}",
                  "description": "AUTO \u2014 set by Step 1a pre-request"
                },
                {
                  "key": "redirect_uri",
                  "value": "https://oauth.pstmn.io/v1/callback",
                  "description": "Must match the redirect_uri registered on the Super Banking User app"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/token",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "auth",
                "pingone",
                "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
                "as",
                "token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Exchanges the PKCE authorization code for the Subject Token (Token 1).\n\nPingOne validates:\n- `code` matches the flow that was completed in Steps 1a-1c\n- `code_verifier` matches the `code_challenge` sent in Step 1a (PKCE proof)\n- `redirect_uri` matches the registered value on the app\n\nThe Subject Token will have:\n- `aud = https://{{ENDUSER_AUDIENCE}}` (ENDUSER_AUDIENCE)\n- `may_act.sub = PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID` (required for Step 2 Token Exchange)\n\nIf `invalid_grant`: the code expired \u2014 rerun Steps 1a, 1b, 1c.\nIf `may_act` missing: run **Utility \u2014 Set mayAct on User** (needs Token 3), then rerun Steps 1a-1d."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = (pm.environment.get('auth_code') || pm.collectionVariables.get('auth_code'));",
                  "if (!code || code.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1d] auth_code is empty. Run Steps 1a, 1b, and 1c first.');",
                  "}",
                  "const verifier = (pm.environment.get('pkce_code_verifier') || pm.collectionVariables.get('pkce_code_verifier'));",
                  "if (!verifier || verifier.trim() === '') {",
                  "    throw new Error('[Step 1d] pkce_code_verifier is empty. Run Step 1a first.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Step 1d: Status 200 \u2014 token issued', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code !== 200) {",
                  "    console.error('[Step 1d] Error:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "    if (json.error === 'invalid_grant') {",
                  "        console.error('[Step 1d] Auth code expired or already used. Rerun Steps 1a -> 1b -> 1c.');",
                  "    }",
                  "    return;",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Step 1d: access_token present', () => pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('subject_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('subject_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_code', '');  // clear used code",
                  "    pm.environment.set('auth_code', '');  // clear used code",
                  "    console.log('[Step 1d] subject_token saved. auth_code cleared.');",
                  "",
                  "    // Decode and validate",
                  "    const parts = json.access_token.split('.');",
                  "    if (parts.length === 3) {",
                  "        try {",
                  "            const payload = JSON.parse(atob(parts[1].replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')));",
                  "            console.log('[Step 1d] Subject Token claims:', JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2));",
                  "",
                  "            if (payload.sub) {",
                  "                pm.collectionVariables.set('user_sub', payload.sub);",
                  "                pm.environment.set('user_sub', payload.sub);",
                  "                console.log('[Step 1d] user_sub saved:', payload.sub);",
                  "            }",
                  "",
                  "            const aud = Array.isArray(payload.aud) ? payload.aud : [payload.aud];",
                  "            pm.test('Step 1d: aud = ENDUSER_AUDIENCE ', () => {",
                  "                pm.expect(aud).to.include(pm.collectionVariables.get('ENDUSER_AUDIENCE'));",
                  "            });",
                  "",
                  "            pm.test('Step 1d: may_act claim present', () => {",
                  "                pm.expect(payload).to.have.property('may_act');",
                  "                pm.expect(payload.may_act).to.have.property('sub');",
                  "            });",
                  "",
                  "            if (payload.may_act) {",
                  "                const expectedActorId = pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID');",
                  "                console.log('[Step 1d] may_act.sub =', payload.may_act.sub, '| expected:', expectedActorId);",
                  "                pm.test('Step 1d: may_act.sub === PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID', () => {",
                  "                    pm.expect(payload.may_act.sub).to.equal(expectedActorId);",
                  "                });",
                  "            } else {",
                  "                console.warn('[Step 1d] WARNING: may_act missing. Run Utility \u2014 Set mayAct on User (needs Token 3 from Step 3), then rerun Steps 1a-1d.');",
                  "            }",
                  "        } catch (e) {",
                  "            console.error('[Step 1d] Could not decode JWT:', e.message);",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 2 \u2014 MCP Token (RFC 8693 Token Exchange #1)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            {
              "key": "grant_type",
              "value": "urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_id",
              "value": "{{PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_secret",
              "value": "{{PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_SECRET}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "subject_token",
              "value": "{{subject_token}}",
              "description": "Subject Token from Step 1"
            },
            {
              "key": "subject_token_type",
              "value": "urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token"
            },
            {
              "key": "requested_token_type",
              "value": "urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token"
            },
            {
              "key": "audience",
              "value": "{{MCP_RESOURCE_URI}}",
              "description": "{{MCP_RESOURCE_URI}} (set in shared environment)"
            },
            {
              "key": "scope",
              "value": "banking:accounts:read banking:transactions:read banking:transactions:write"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/token",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "auth",
            "pingone",
            "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
            "as",
            "token"
          ]
        },
        "description": "RFC 8693 token exchange: exchanges the Subject Token for an MCP-scoped token. The resulting MCP Token has: aud = MCP_RESOURCE_URI, act.sub = PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID (the delegating BFF client), scope narrowed to MCP scopes. Saves mcp_token to collection variable. Required before Step 3."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Step 2: Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Step 2: access_token present', () => pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "",
              "if (json.access_token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('mcp_token', json.access_token);",
              "    pm.environment.set('mcp_token', json.access_token);",
              "    console.log('[Step 2] mcp_token saved');",
              "",
              "    const parts = json.access_token.split('.');",
              "    if (parts.length === 3) {",
              "        try {",
              "            const payload = JSON.parse(atob(parts[1].replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')));",
              "            console.log('[Step 2] MCP Token claims:', JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2));",
              "",
              "            // Verify audience",
              "            const aud = Array.isArray(payload.aud) ? payload.aud : [payload.aud];",
              "            pm.test('Step 2: aud = MCP_RESOURCE_URI', () => {",
              "                pm.expect(aud).to.include(pm.collectionVariables.get('MCP_RESOURCE_URI'));",
              "            });",
              "",
              "            // Verify act claim (delegation proof)",
              "            pm.test('Step 2: act claim present', () => {",
              "                pm.expect(payload).to.have.property('act');",
              "                pm.expect(payload.act).to.have.property('sub');",
              "            });",
              "",
              "            if (payload.act) {",
              "                const expectedActorId = pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID');",
              "                console.log('[Step 2] act.sub =', payload.act.sub, '| expected:', expectedActorId);",
              "                pm.test('Step 2: act.sub === PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID', () => {",
              "                    pm.expect(payload.act.sub).to.equal(expectedActorId);",
              "                });",
              "            }",
              "",
              "            // Verify sub preserved from Subject Token",
              "            const userSub = (pm.environment.get('user_sub') || pm.collectionVariables.get('user_sub'));",
              "            if (userSub) {",
              "                pm.test('Step 2: sub preserved from Subject Token', () => {",
              "                    pm.expect(payload.sub).to.equal(userSub);",
              "                });",
              "            }",
              "        } catch (e) {",
              "            console.error('[Step 2] Could not decode JWT payload:', e.message);",
              "        }",
              "    }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 3 \u2014 PingOne API Token (Client Credentials)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            {
              "key": "grant_type",
              "value": "client_credentials"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_id",
              "value": "{{MCP_CLIENT_ID}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "client_secret",
              "value": "{{MCP_CLIENT_SECRET}}"
            },
            {
              "key": "scope",
              "value": "p1:read:user p1:update:user"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/token",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "auth",
            "pingone",
            "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
            "as",
            "token"
          ]
        },
        "description": "MCP service client obtains a PingOne Management API token via client_credentials grant. Required to call the PingOne user lookup API in Step 4. Saves pingone_api_token to collection variable."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Step 3: Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Step 3: access_token present', () => pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "",
              "if (json.access_token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('pingone_api_token', json.access_token);",
              "    pm.environment.set('pingone_api_token', json.access_token);",
              "    console.log('[Step 3] pingone_api_token saved');",
              "",
              "    const parts = json.access_token.split('.');",
              "    if (parts.length === 3) {",
              "        try {",
              "            const payload = JSON.parse(atob(parts[1].replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')));",
              "            console.log('[Step 3] PingOne API Token claims:', JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2));",
              "",
              "            // Verify audience",
              "            const aud = Array.isArray(payload.aud) ? payload.aud : [payload.aud];",
              "            pm.test('Step 3: aud = https://api.pingone.com', () => {",
              "                pm.expect(aud).to.include(pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_API_AUDIENCE'));",
              "            });",
              "",
              "            // Verify scope",
              "            pm.test('Step 3: scope includes p1:read:user', () => {",
              "                pm.expect(payload.scope).to.include('p1:read:user');",
              "            });",
              "",
              "            // Token 3 should NOT have a sub (service token, not user token)",
              "            if (payload.sub) {",
              "                console.warn('[Step 3] Unexpected sub claim on PingOne API Token:', payload.sub);",
              "            }",
              "        } catch (e) {",
              "            console.error('[Step 3] Could not decode JWT payload:', e.message);",
              "        }",
              "    }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 4 \u2014 User Lookup (PingOne Management API)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{pingone_api_token}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://api.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/v1/environments/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/users/{{user_sub}}",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "api",
            "pingone",
            "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "v1",
            "environments",
            "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
            "users",
            "{{user_sub}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Looks up the user in the PingOne Management API using the subject's sub claim. Returns user profile attributes (username, name, email, custom claims). Requires pingone_api_token from Step 3."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Step 4: Status 200 \u2014 user lookup succeeded', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Step 4: id matches user_sub', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(json.id).to.equal((pm.environment.get('user_sub') || pm.collectionVariables.get('user_sub')));",
              "});",
              "",
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "    console.log('[Step 4] User object:', JSON.stringify(json, null, 2));",
              "",
              "    // Check mayAct custom attribute is set",
              "    if (json.mayAct) {",
              "        console.log('[Step 4] mayAct on user record:', JSON.stringify(json.mayAct));",
              "        pm.test('Step 4: mayAct.sub matches PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID', () => {",
              "            pm.expect(json.mayAct.sub).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('PINGONE_CORE_CLIENT_ID'));",
              "        });",
              "    } else {",
              "        console.warn('[Step 4] WARNING: mayAct attribute missing from user record. Token Exchange will fail at runtime. Set it via /demo-data \u2192 Enable may_act or via PATCH /users/{id}.');",
              "    }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Utility \u2014 Decode Token (paste any JWT)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            {
              "key": "token",
              "value": "{{subject_token}}",
              "description": "Replace with any of: subject_token, mcp_token, pingone_api_token"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://auth.pingone.{{PINGONE_REGION}}/{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}/as/introspect",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "auth",
            "pingone",
            "{{PINGONE_REGION}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "{{PINGONE_ENVIRONMENT_ID}}",
            "as",
            "introspect"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Decodes and displays the claims in any JWT token. Paste the token you want to inspect into the token collection variable (or the body). Useful for verifying the act claim chain, aud, scope, and exp at each step."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
